be%20completely%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20long-standing%20hypothesis%20held%20that%20Spanish%20conquistadors%20had%20picked%20up%20the%20sexually-transmitted%20infection%20(STI)%20and%20introduced%20it%20to%20Europe%20in%20the%20late%201400s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20paper%20published%20Wednesday%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D5665415566a290e3874cf144166e9a89d6ce0502d9dfc72d2b75f86ed975163d%26postID%3D65b22af6d40d73d7027d0397%26postSlug%3Dcolumbus-likely-didnt-bring-syphilis-to-europe-ancient-dna-suggests-2024-1%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-023-06965-x%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENature%3C%2Fa%3E%20adds%20to%20a%20mounting%20body%20of%20evidence%20that%20the%20conquistadors%20didn't%20spread%20the%20disease%20following%20their%20invasion%20of%20now%20South%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20bacteria%20may%20have%20emerged%20a%20lot%20sooner%20than%20previously%20thought%2C%20Verena%20Sch%C3%BCnemann%2C%20professor%20of%20Paleogenetics%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Basel%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20we%20cannot%20prove%20it%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20it%20doesn't%20work%20yet.%20But%20it%20seems%20that%20there's%20a%20much%20more%20complex%20story%20developing%20than%20these%20hypotheses%20are%20capturing%20currently%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22895%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20engraving%20shows%20columbus%20speaking%20with%20the%20then%20king%20of%20Spain%20after%20his%20first%20expedition.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b25a6bf4b446f3be9d014d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22643%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIllustration%20shows%20Christopher%20Columbus%20upon%20his%20return%20from%20the%20'New%20World'%20at%20the%20royal%20court%2C%20Barcelona%2C%20Spain%2C%20February%201493.%3Cp%3EInterim%20Archives%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20timing%20of%20the%20arrival%20of%20syphilis%20in%20Europe%20is%20suspicious%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20at%20historical%20literature%2C%20you%20would%20think%20syphilis%20definitely%20arrived%20with%20the%20conquistadors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20big%20outbreak%20of%20syphilis%20in%20Europe%20in%20the%20late%201400s%2C%20mostly%20in%20harbor%20towns%2C%20seemingly%20out%20of%20the%20blue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20lined%20up%20suspiciously%20with%20the%20return%20of%20sailors%20who%20accompanied%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3956094%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Columbus%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20his%20voyage%20to%20South%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecords%20of%20syphilis%20outbreaks%20before%20then%20were%20poor.%20Later%20excavations%20revealed%20bones%20in%20South%20America%20that%20carried%20lesions%20typically%20associated%20with%20a%20syphilis%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltogether%2C%20this%20prompted%20historians%20to%20look%20at%20the%20voyage%20as%20an%20early%20example%20of%20how%20infections%20can%20spread%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcept%2C%20it's%20likely%20not%20that%20simple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20observations%20revealed%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Fmedieval-dna-suggests-columbus-didn-t-trigger-syphilis-epidemic-europe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskeletons%20found%20in%20European%3C%2Fa%3E%20sites%20may%20also%20carry%20lesions%20typical%20of%20a%20syphilis%20infection%2C%20long%20before%20the%20first%20contact%20with%20pre-Columbian%20indigenous%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20plot%20thickens%2C%20scientists%20have%20started%20looking%20to%20more%20modern%20methods%20of%20investigation%20to%20uncover%20what%20really%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDNA%20analysis%20reveals%20a%20more%20complicated%20story%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20the%20history%20of%20syphilis%20better%2C%20Sch%C3%BCnemann%20and%20her%20colleagues%20looked%20at%202%2C000-year-old%20bones%20carrying%20the%20characteristic%20lesions%2C%20which%20were%20found%20about%2020%20years%20ago%20in%20now%20Brazil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20drilled%20tiny%20holes%20in%20the%20lesions%20using%20dentists'%20tools%20and%20extracted%20the%20ancient%20DNA%20left%20behind%20by%20the%20bacteria%20in%20the%20bone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20found%20that%20some%20of%20these%20lesions%20weren't%20caused%20by%20the%20bacteria%20behind%20sexually-transmitted%20syphilis%20but%20by%20a%20closely%20related%20cousin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20microbe%20is%20very%20similar%20to%20the%20one%20behind%20syphilis%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20part%20of%20the%20same%20family%2C%20called%20Treponema%20%E2%80%94%20it%20causes%20a%20completely%20different%20disease%2C%20called%20Bejel%2C%20which%20is%20not%20sexually%20transmitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20still%20around%20today%2C%20mostly%20in%20Asia%20and%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20actually%20didn't%20expect%20to%20find%20it%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sch%C3%BCnemann.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUsually%20it's%20in%20arid%20regions%2C%20not%20so%20much%20in%20those%20humid%20coastal%2C%20tropical%20region.%20That's%20why%20we%20were%20quite%20surprised%20%E2%80%94%20this%20is%20a%20completely%20different%20environment%20than%20where%20you%20expect%20to%20find%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20suggests%20that%20the%20bones%20lesions%20alone%20don't%20guarantee%20that%20syphilis%20was%20present%20in%20South%20America%20before%20Columbus%2C%20poking%20holes%20in%20the%20evidence%20used%20to%20support%20the%20hypothesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20is%20%26quot%3Breally%20exciting%20because%20it%20is%20the%20first%20truly%20ancient%20treponemal%20DNA%20that%20has%20been%20recovered%20from%20archaeological%20human%20remains%20that%20are%20more%20than%20a%20few%20hundred%20years%20old%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brenda%20Baker%20at%20Arizona%20State%20University%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newscientist.com%2Farticle%2F2413971-syphilis-like-bacteria-found-in-2000-year-old-human-remains-in-brazil%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20New%20Scientist.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222309%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%203D%20rendering%20shows%20a%20spiral-shaped%20bacterium%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b251346c8f0a134f79f240%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221299%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%203D%20rendering%20of%20a%20Treponema%20microbe.%20The%20characteristic%20spiral%20shape%20is%20typical%20of%20the%20bacteria%20that%20cause%20syphilis%20or%20Bejel.%3Cp%3Ebbevren%2FiStock%2FGetty%20Images%20Plus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20mystery%20remains%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20don't%20decisively%20close%20the%20door%20on%20the%20Columbus%20theory.%20But%20they%20do%20offer%20precious%20clues%20to%20better%20understand%20what%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20helps%20us%20indirectly%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sch%C3%BCnemann.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20ancient%20genome%2C%20Sch%C3%BCnemann%20and%20colleagues%20were%20able%20to%20discover%20that%20the%20whole%20Treponema%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Efamily%20is%20much%20older%20than%20had%20ever%20been%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20suggests%20that%20these%20closely-related%20bacteria%20have%20a%20common%20ancestor%20about%2014%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20said%20Sch%C3%BCnemann.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20these%20bacteria%20could%20easily%20have%20traveled%20around%20the%20world%20several%20times%20with%20the%20different%20human%20migrations%2C%20much%20earlier%20than%20Columbus's%20expeditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can%20now%20play%20around%20and%20say%2C%20okay%2C%20which%20hypothesis%20can%20we%20maybe%20develop%20from%20that%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Sch%C3%BCnemann%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Sch%C3%BCnemann%2C%20it's%20more%20likely%20that%20the%20bacteria%20causing%20syphilis%2C%20Bejel%2C%20and%20other%20cousins%20of%20the%20Treponema%20family%20were%20already%20around%20in%20Europe%2C%20India%2C%20and%20the%20Americas%2C%20long%20before%20the%20first%20contact%20between%20Columbus%20and%20indigenous%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there's%20definitely%20a%20potential%20that%20they%20were%20around%20before%20the%20contact%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20be%20interesting%2C%20she%20said%2C%20to%20try%20to%20do%20the%20same%20analyses%20on%20the%20European%20bones%20carrying%20lesions%20and%20to%20find%20even%20older%20samples%20that%20could%20draw%20a%20better%20picture%20of%20the%20Treponema%20family%20tree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20importance%20of%20the%20work%20goes%20beyond%20solving%20this%20historical%20mystery.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgonorrhea-syphilis-cdc-pandemic-lockdowns-did-not-slow-spread-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESyphilis%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20its%20cousins%20are%20still%20rampant%20in%20the%20world%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20they%20are%20kept%20under%20control%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Fyaws%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eantibiotics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20are%20learning%20quickly%20how%20to%20side-step%20the%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226792%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20shows%20pox%20and%20necrosis%20linked%20with%20untreated%20syphilis.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b24e4b43bb77284ba0833a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224433%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20from%201868%20shows%20what%20can%20happen%20when%20syphilis%20is%20not%20treated.%3Cp%3EFlorilegius%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELeft%20untreated%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fstd%2Fsyphilis%2Fthe-facts%2Fsyphilis_bro_508.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esyphilis%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20cause%20permanent%20damage%20to%20the%20heart%2C%20brain%2C%20and%20other%20internal%20organs.%20Bejel%2C%20or%20yaws%2C%20is%20a%20childhood%20disease%20that%20can%20be%20disfiguring%20and%20debilitating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20looking%20back%20at%20how%20it%20has%20evolved%20with%20humans%20in%20the%20past%2C%20for%20instance%20how%20the%20microbes%20pass%20genetic%20information%20back%20and%20forth%2C%20we%20can%20better%20predict%20how%20it%20will%20progress%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20now%20to%20this%20increase%20in%20antibiotic%20resistance%20and%20so%20on%2C%20then%20it%20can%20help%20in%20the%20future%20to%20develop%20new%20strategies%20to%20fight%20this%20bacteria%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolumbus-likely-didnt-bring-syphilis-to-europe-ancient-dna-suggests-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706197008000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b22baaf4b446f3be9cf4b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolumbus-likely-didnt-bring-syphilis-to-europe-ancient-dna-suggests-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20long-standing%20theory%20that%20Columbus%20caused%20a%20devastating%20outbreak%20of%20syphilis%20when%20his%20expedition%20came%20back%20from%20the%20Americas%20is%20falling%20apart.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mguenot%40businessinsider.com%20(Marianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolumbus-likely-didnt-bring-syphilis-to-europe-ancient-dna-suggests-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampU