20rents%20during%20the%20pandemic%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20shortage%20of%20affordable%20units.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20estimated%2012.1%20million%20Americans%20are%20spending%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freports%2Ffiles%2FHarvard_JCHS_Americas_Rental_Housing_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalf%20their%20income%20on%20rent%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20utilities%2C%20a%20study%20from%20Harvard's%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20estimates%20from%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau%2C%20the%20study%20reports%20this%20is%20more%20people%20than%20at%20any%20other%20time%20for%20which%20data%20is%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%201.5%20million%20more%20people%20since%202019%20spending%20that%20proportion%20of%20their%20income%20on%20housing%2C%20the%20researchers%20say%20the%20increase%20was%20%26quot%3Bfueled%20by%20rapidly%20rising%20rents%20during%20the%20pandemic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20defines%20spending%20over%2050%25%20on%20rent%20and%20utilities%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bseverely%20cost-burdened%20household%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20those%20who%20spend%20at%20least%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20are%20considered%20to%20be%20cost-burdened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202014%20and%202019%2C%20the%20number%20of%20renters%20defined%20as%20cost-burdened%2C%20but%20not%20%26quot%3Bseverely%26quot%3B%20cost-burdened%20dropped%20by%20an%20estimated%20883%2C000%2C%20to%20around%2020.4%20million%2C%20but%20the%20figure%20has%20risen%20sharply%20amid%20the%20COVID%20pandemic%2C%20with%2022.4%20million%20renters%20now%20considered%20cost-burdened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.6%20million%20more%20people%20are%20cost-burdened%20than%20in%202001%2C%20the%20earliest%20year%20cited%20by%20the%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies%2C%20the%20research%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chart%20showing%20the%20rising%20number%20of%20renters%20spending%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b270b0f4b446f3be9d0782%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221248%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20chart%20showing%20the%20rising%20number%20of%20renters%20spending%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent.%3Cp%3EThe%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies%20of%20Harvard%20University%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECea%20Weaver%2C%20a%20Housing%20Justice%20for%20All%20campaign%20coordinator%2C%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20definitely%20worse%20than%20it's%20ever%20been.%20Middle-class%20people%2C%20lower-middle-class%20people%2C%20working-class%20people%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F01%2F25%2Frealestate%2Frent-prices-housing.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecannot%20afford%20their%20rent%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20tight%20budgets%20force%20financially%20vulnerable%20renters%20to%20make%20dreadful%20choices%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20survey%20says%2C%20noting%20that%20those%20who%20are%20severely%20cost-burdened%20spend%20significantly%20less%20of%20their%20income%20on%20food%20and%20healthcare%20than%20their%20unburdened%20counterparts.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BOthers%20may%20end%20up%20living%20in%20overcrowded%20or%20structurally%20inadequate%20conditions%2C%20threatening%20their%20health%20and%20well-being%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20survey%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20those%20who%20earn%20between%20%2430%2C000%20to%20%2444%2C999%20a%20year%2C%20the%20study%20found%20two-thirds%20were%20cost-burdened%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20an%20increase%20of%2015.1%20percentage%20points%20from%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20since%202001%2C%20nearly%20twice%20as%20many%20households%20with%20incomes%20of%20%2445%2C000%20to%20%2474%2C999%20are%20burdened%2C%20to%20the%20tune%20of%2041%25%2C%20the%20st