ized%20rate%20of%204.9%25.%20The%20latest%20figure%20was%20also%20above%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investing.com%2Feconomic-calendar%2Fgdp-375%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eforecast%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202.0%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompared%20to%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%20the%20deceleration%20in%20real%20GDP%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20primarily%20reflected%20slowdowns%20in%20private%20inventory%20investment%2C%20federal%20government%20spending%2C%20residential%20fixed%20investment%2C%20and%20consumer%20spending%2C%26quot%3B%20Thursday's%20news%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fc5nlq%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Change%20in%20real%20GDP%20from%20previous%20quarter%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20areas%20saw%20increases%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%2C%20including%20exports%20and%20government%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increase%20in%20real%20GDP%20reflected%20increases%20in%20consumer%20spending%2C%20exports%2C%20state%20and%20local%20government%20spending%2C%20nonresidential%20fixed%20investment%2C%20federal%20government%20spending%2C%20private%20inventory%20investment%2C%20and%20residential%20fixed%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20news%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20positive%20GDP%20numbers%20for%20the%20past%20few%20quarters%20show%20that%20the%20US%20has%20so%20far%20avoided%20a%20recession%20%E2%80%94%20although%20it's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20GDP%20isn't%20the%20only%20thing%20to%20consider%20when%20looking%20at%20a%20recession.%20There%20are%20different%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fresearch%2Fbusiness-cycle-dating%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20indicators%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20data%20involving%20employment%2C%20that%20economists%20consider%20when%20evaluating%20the%20business%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NABE%20(National%20Association%20for%20Business%20Economics)%20Business%20Conditions%20Survey%20shows%20a%20higher%20share%20of%20respondents%20are%20also%20feeling%20more%20optimistic%20about%20the%20country%20not%20experiencing%20a%20recession%20soon.%20The%20survey%20was%20done%20from%20December%2028%2C%202023%2C%20to%20January%209%2C%202024.%20A%20post%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnabe.com%2FNABE%2FSurveys%2FBusiness_Conditions_Surveys%2FJanuary-2024-Business-Conditions-Survey-Summary.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENABE%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20it%20stated%2091%25%20of%20survey%20%26quot%3Brespondents%20assign%20a%20probability%20of%2050%25%20or%20less%20to%20the%20U.S.%20entering%20a%20recession%20over%20the%20next%2012%20months%2C%20up%20from%2079%25%20of%20respondents%20who%20held%20this%20view%20in%20the%20October%20survey.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20Rattner%2C%20chairman%20and%20CEO%20of%20Willett%20Advisors%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DKCbGVmwOsKQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBloomberg%20interview%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20predicting%20a%20recession%26quot%3B%20but%20given%20we're%20close%20to%20the%20edge%2C%20it%20could%20go%20either%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20signs%20of%20the%20economy%20starting%20to%20weaken%20a%20little%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20Rattner%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20jobs%20market%20is%20weakening%20a%20little%20bit.%20Retail%20sales%20are%20weakening%20on%20an%20inflation-adjusted%20basis%20a%20little%20bit.%20You%20do%20see%20signs%20of%20stresses%20and%20strains%2C%20savings%20rates%2C%20credit%20card%20usage%2C%20subprime%20auto%20delinquencies%2C%20things%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERattner%20said%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20question%26quot%3B%20that%20last%20year%20the%20economy%20was%20robust%20compared%20to%20expectations%20partly%20because%20there%20was%20more%20purchasing%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonfarm%20payroll%20growth%20also%20suggests%20a%20strong%20jobs%20market%20last%20year%20despite%20smaller%20job%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPayroll%20employment%20rose%20by%202.7%20million%20in%202023%20(an%20average%20monthly%20gain%20of%20225%2C000)%2C%20less%20than%20the%20increase%20of%204.8%20million%20in%202022%20(an%20average%20monthly%20gain%20of%20399%2C000)%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20news%20release%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20real%20GDP%20saw%20a%20larger%20increase%20last%20year%20than%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%202.5%25%20in%202023%20compared%20to%201.9%25%20in%202022.%20An%20increase%20in%20consumer%20spending%20was%20just%20one%20of%20the%20areas%20behind%20the%20increase%20in%20real%20GDP%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increase%20in%20real%20GDP%20in%202023%20primarily%20reflected%20increases%20in%20consumer%20spending%2C%20nonresidential%20fixed%20investment%2C%20state%20and%20local%20government%20spending%2C%20exports%2C%20and%20federal%20government%20spending%20that%20were%20partly%20offset%20by%20decreases%20in%20residential%20fixed%20investment%20and%20inventory%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20news%20release%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-gdp-fourth-quarter-of-2023-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706189765000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b12c996c8f0a134f79912e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-gdp-fourth-quarter-of-2023-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20data%20release%20showed%20real%20GDP%20rose%20at%20an%20annua