c%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F08%2FKandhamal_Reuters.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20Christian%20couple%20from%20Karnataka%E2%80%99s%20Bijapur%20was%20allegedly%20beaten%20up%20by%20a%20group%20of%20men%20for%20practicing%20their%20faith.%20They%20were%20warned%20of%20further%20violence%20if%20they%20continued%20with%20their%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20came%20to%20light%20after%20Vijayalakshmi%20and%20her%20husband%20Ashok%20Chavan%2C%20the%20victims%2C%20approached%20a%20local%20court%20to%20lodge%20their%20complaint.%20Police%20registered%20a%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%2C%20based%20on%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20under%20Sections%20143%2C%20147%2C%20509%2C%20323%2C%20504%2C%20506%2C%20and%20149%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20per%20the%20constitution%2C%20I%20have%20the%20right%20to%20practice%20Christianity%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Vijayalakshmi%20in%20her%20complaint.%20According%20to%20her%2C%20she%20has%20been%20facing%20harassment%20from%20a%20group%20of%20men%2C%20including%20abusive%20comments%20being%20hurled%20at%20her%2C%20threats%20to%20%E2%80%9Cruin%E2%80%9D%20her%20life%20and%20her%20family%E2%80%99s%2C%20and%20even%20being%20warned%20of%20getting%20her%20food%20security%20card%2C%20Aadhar%20Card%2C%20and%20other%20government%20documents%20cancelled.%20The%20men%20also%20threatened%20to%20get%20her%20fired%20from%20her%20job%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FIR%20named%20Ravi%20Darappa%20Lamani%2C%20Suresh%20Shivappa%20Lamani%2C%20Rajshekhar%20Lamani%2C%20Puneet%20Lamani%2C%20Parasu%20Ratnappa%20Lamani%2C%20and%20Dhanasing%20Lamani%20as%20accused.%20The%20attack%20on%20Vijayalakshmi%20and%20her%20husband%20took%20place%20a%20day%20after%20they%20were%20accused%20locally%20of%20%E2%80%9Cforced%20conversion%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20campaign%20was%20run%20against%20them%20on%20social%20media%20platforms%20locally%20and%20across%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVijaylaxmi%20is%20an%20Accredited%20Social%20Health%20Activist%20(ASHA)%2C%20a%20government-accredited%20community-level%20healthcare%20worker%20involved%20in%20raising%20awareness%20about%20basic%20healthcare%20by%20going%20door-to-door.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChristian%20Solidarity%20Worldwide%20(CSW)%2C%20an%20organisation%20working%20for%20the%20Christian%20community%20worldwide%2C%20reported%20that%20some%20villagers%20objected%20to%20a%20Christian%20woman%20entering%20their%20houses%20and%20threatened%20her%20family%2C%20attempting%20to%20get%20her%20fired%20from%20her%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20forced%20conversion%20allegations%2C%20other%20Christians%20in%20the%20Uppaladinni%20area%20filed%20a%20complaint%20at%20the%20Basavana%20Bagewadi%20Municipal%20Police%20Station.%20This%20is%20not%20an%20isolated%20incident%2C%20as%20three%20other%20Christian%20families%20from%20Uppaladinni%2C%20attending%20the%20same%20church%20as%20Chavhan%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20have%20also%20faced%20harassment%20this%20month.%20On%20January%203%2C%20the%20community%20chief%20directed%20local%20utility%20services%20to%20cut%20off%20electricity%20and%20water%20supply%20for%20these%20families%2C%20publicly%20warning%20them%20that%20they%20would%20be%20killed%20if%20they%20continued%20to%20follow%20Jesus%20Christ.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECSW%E2%80%99s%20founder%20president%2C%20Mervyn%20Thomas%2C%20expressed%20concern%2C%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CCSW%20is%20alarmed%20for%20the%20Christians%20in%20Uppaladinni%20who%20have%20been%20singled%20out%2C%20harassed%2C%20and%20attacked%20due%20to%20their%20beliefs.%20We%20urge%20the%20police%20to%20thoroughly%20investigate%20the%20perpetrators%20who%20assaulted%20Mr.%20and%20Mrs.%20Chavhan%20and%20ensure%20that%20all%20attackers%20are%20brought%20to%20justice.%20This%20is%20part%20of%20a%20growing%20trend%20of%20social%20hostility%20towards%20religious%20minorities%20across%20India%20that%20authorities%20must%20address%20urgently.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20over%20300%20churches%20were%20burnt%20down%20in%20India%2C%20and%20there%20were%20525%20attacks%20against%20Christians%20in%20just%20the%20first%20eight%20months%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202012%20and%202022%2C%20the%20recorded%20incidents%20increased%20fourfold.%20The%20first%20significant%20rise%20occurred%20in%202016%2C%20with%20247%20incidents%20detailed%20in%20the%20EFI%20report.%20This%20number%20continued%20to%20increase%20in%20the%20following%20years%2C%20reaching%20505%20incidents%20in%202021%20and%20further%20rising%20to%20599%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20United%20Christian%20Forum%20(UCF)%20report%2C%20violence%20against%20Christians%20occurred%20in%2023%20states%20in%202023.%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20led%20with%20155%20incidents%2C%20followed%20by%20Chhattisgarh%20with%2084%2C%20Jharkhand%20with%2035%2C%20Haryana%20with%2032%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20with%2021%2C%20Punjab%20with%2012%2C%20Karnataka%20with%2010%2C%20Bihar%20with%209%2C%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20with%208%2C%20Gujarat%20with%207%2C%20Uttarakhand%20with%204%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20with%203%2C%20West%20Bengal%20with%203%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20with%203%2C%20Maharashtra%20with%203%2C%20Odisha%20with%202%2C%20Delhi%20with%202%2C%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Assam%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20and%20Goa%20with%20one%20incident%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706189710000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F08%2FKandhamal_Reuters.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fin-karnatakas-bijapur-christian-couple-beaten-up-for-allegedly-practising-faith%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20group%20of%20men%20who%20were%20behind%20the%20attack%20warned%20the%20woman%2C%20who%20works%20as%20an%20ASHA%20worker%2C%20of%20getting%20her%20fired%20from%20her%20job%20as%20well%20getting%20her%20food%20security%20card%20canceled.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fin-karnatakas-bijapur-christian-couple-beaten-up-for-allegedly-practising-faith%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Study%20estimates%20that%2064%2C000%20women%20have%20become%20pregnant%20from%20rape%20in%20states%20that%20put%20in%20abortion%20bans%20after%20the%20end%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20stock%20image%20shows%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20touching%20her%20baby%20bump.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b24dd7f4b446f3be9cffbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20stock%20image%20shows%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20touching%20her%20baby%20bump.%3Cp%3Ed3sign%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20study%20estimates%20that%2064%2C000%2B%20pregnancies%20caused%20by%20rape%20have%20occurred%20in%20states%20banning%20abortion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20research%20aimed%20to%20look%20at%20how%20rape%20survivors%20are%20impacted%20by%20the%20overturning%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20study%20author%20said%20he%20was%C2%A0%26quot%3Bhorrified%26quot%3B%20by%20how%20many%20rape%20victims%20lacked%20access%20to%20abortions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamainternalmedicine%2Ffullarticle%2F2814274%3FguestAccessKey%3De429b9a8-72ac-42ed-8dbc-599b0f509890%26utm_source%3DFor_The_Media%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_campaign%3Dftm_links%26utm_content%3Dtfl%26utm_term%3D012424%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20on%20Wednesday%20in%20JAMA%20Internal%20Medicine%20%3C%2Fa%3Eestimated%20that%20over%2064%2C000%20pregnancies%20were%20caused%20by%20rape%20in%20the%2014%20states%20with%20abortion%20bans%20since%20July%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESamuel%20Dickman%2C%20Planned%20Parenthood%20Montana's%20medical%20director%2C%20along%20with%20his%20team%2C%20attempted%20to%20quantify%20the%20number%20of%20rape-related%20pregnancies%20in%20states%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmale-lawmakers-drove-trigger-law-abortion-bans-for-women-chart-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabortion%20bans%3C%2Fa%3E%20triggered%20by%20the%20overturning%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Froe-v-wade%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoe%20v.%20Wade.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-abortion-decision-final-ruling-scotus-roe-v-wade-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20overturned%20the%20landmark%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20legalized%20abortion%20across%20the%20US%20in%20June%202022%2C%20granting%20states%20the%20authority%20to%20determine%20their%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpro-life-let-them-live-promised-women-money-cancel-abortion-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabortion%20laws.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20stands%2C%2014%20states%20have%20implemented%20total%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fabortion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabortion%3C%2Fa%3E%20bans%20following%20the%20Dobbs%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20in%20these%2014%20states%2C%20an%20estimated%2064%2C565%20pregnancies%20were%20linked%20to%20rape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20these%20(91%25)%20occurred%20in%20states%20without%20exceptions%20that%20allow%20for%20the%20termination%20of%20pregnancies%20in%20cases%20of%20rape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20researchers%2C%20a%20significant%20proportion%20of%20these%20rape-caused%20pregnancies%20occurred%20in%20Texas%20%E2%80%94%2045%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20reach%20the%20estimates%2C%20the%20study%20used%20historic%20data%20from%20the%20US%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(CDC)%20on%20nationwide%20incidents%20of%20vaginal%20rape%20and%20adjusted%20it%20to%20females%20aged%20between%2015%20and%2045%2C%20using%20data%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Justice%20Statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20then%20apportioned%20the%20nationwide%20data%20among%20states%2C%20multiplying%20the%20state-level%20estimates%20by%20the%20fraction%20likely%20to%20result%20in%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20did%20this%20for%20a%20period%20between%20July%201%2C%202022%20%E2%80%94%20the%20week%20after%20the%20Dobbs%20decision%E2%80%94%20and%20January%201%20of%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDickman%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20researcher%20at%20City%20University%20of%20New%20York%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fhealth-shots%2F2024%2F01%2F24%2F1226161416%2Frape-caused-pregnancy-abortion-ban-states%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20NPR%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20his%20team%20was%20shocked%20by%20how%20high%20the%20number%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20horrified%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20news%20outlet.%20%26quot%3BSexual%20assault%20is%20incredibly%20common%20%E2%80%94%20I%20knew%20that%20in%20a%20general%20sense.%20But%20to%20be%20confronted%20with%20these%20estimates%20that%20are%20so%20high%20in%20states%20where%20there's%20no%20meaningful%20abortion%20access%3F%20It's%20hard%20to%20comprehend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20acknowledged%20some%20limitations%2C%20including%20the%20difficulty%20of%20obtaining%20accurate%20data%20on%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20stigmatized%20experiences.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERachel%20Perry%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20OB-GYN%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Irvine%2C%20who%20was%20not%20associated%20with%20the%20study%2C%20told%20NPR%20that%20it%20is%20also%20worth%20noting%20that%20not%20everyone%20who%20becomes%20pregnant%20from%20rape%20necessarily%20wants%20an%20abortion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20Perry%20said%20that%20the%20study%20shows%20that%20even%20if%20the%20numbers%20aren't%20exact%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20a%20huge%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F64000-pregnancies-from-rape-states-abortion-bans-study-roe-wade-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706189699000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b24eb443bb77284ba0838a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F64000-pregnancies-from-rape-states-abortion-bans-study-roe-wade-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20states%20that%20implemented%20abortion%20bans%20after%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%20was%20overturned%2C%20over%2064%2C000%20women%20have%20become%20pregnant%20by%20rape%2C%20new%20study%20estimates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzitser%40businessinsider.com%20(Joshua%20Zitser)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F64000-pregnancies-from-rape-states-abortion-bans-study-roe-wade-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%202013-2022%2C%20Over%20800%20Died%20Every%20Year%20On%20Average%20Due%20to%20Exposure%20to%20Cold%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25184736%2F6658972065_82aa80f2fa_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20On%20average%2C%20810%20people%20died%20every%20year%20of%20exposure%20to%20the%20cold%20during%20the%20decade%202013-2022%2C%20according%20to%20data%20released%20by%20the%20National%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%20(NCRB)%20and%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fnorth-india-sees-over-800-deaths-a-year-due-to-cold-since-2013-mospi-data-124012401017_1.html%5C%22%3Efirst%20reported%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20decade%20in%20question%2C%202015%20saw%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20deaths%20due%20to%20this%20cause%20at%201%2C149%20and%202021%20the%20lowest%20at%20618.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crime%20data%20repository%20files%20such%20deaths%20under%20the%20category%20%E2%80%98accidental%20deaths%20due%20to%20forces%20of%20nature%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20720%20people%20died%20due%20to%20exposure%20to%20the%20cold%2C%20the%20NCRB%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Faccidental-deaths-suicides-in-india-year-wise.html%3Fyear%3D2022%5C%22%3EAccidental%20Deaths%20and%20Suicides%20in%20India%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20report%20said.%20The%20states%20where%20the%20most%20people%20died%20of%20this%20cause%20in%202022%20are%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(192)%2C%20Punjab%20(123)%20and%20Jharkhand%20(117).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20statistics%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20latest%20environment%20statistics%20report%20says%20that%20in%202022%2C%20the%20average%20number%20of%20cold%20wave%20days%20in%20each%20of%20the%2024%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20of%20the%20country%20that%20were%20listed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mospi.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freports_and_publication%2Fstatistical_publication%2FEnviStats%2FES1_2023_Comp4.pdf%5C%22%3Eadded%20up%20to%2057%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaryana%20reported%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20such%20days%20in%202022%20at%20nine%2C%20followed%20by%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20(seven)%20and%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Telangana%20(six%20each).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20decade%202013-2022%2C%202019%20recorded%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20such%20days%20across%20the%2024%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20at%20103%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20calculated%20that%20in%20this%20decade%2C%20the%20region%20comprising%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20and%20Ladakh%20recorded%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20cold%20wave%20days%20at%2085%2C%20followed%20by%20Haryana%20(79)%2C%20Bihar%20(61)%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(56).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20recorded%2051%20cold%20wave%20days%20in%20this%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimdpune.gov.in%2Fhazardatlas%2Fcold.pdf%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cold%20waves%20occur%20when%20temperatures%20either%20go%20below%20a%20certain%20threshold%20or%20if%20they%20experience%20significant%20decreases%20compared%20to%20regular%20temperatures.%20These%20limits%20vary%20across%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20weather%20briefing%20on%20Thursday%20(January%2025)%20said%20that%20dense%20fog%2C%20cold%20day%20and%20cold%20wave%20conditions%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FIndiametdept%2Fstatus%2F1750469893982683380%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Econtinue%20in%20northern%20India%20for%20the%20next%20two%20days%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minimum%20temperature%20at%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Lodhi%20Road%20weather%20observatory%20dipped%20to%203.1%20%C2%B0C%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20January%2016%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIndia%20Today%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ereported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDense%20fog%20over%20northern%20India%20this%20winter%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Findigo-fined-1-2crore-mumbai-airport-90lakh-for-tarmac-meal%2Farticleshow%2F106938292.cms%5C%22%3Edelay%2C%20diversion%20or%20cancellation%20of%20flights%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20trains.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706189539000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25184736%2F6658972065_82aa80f2fa_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fover-800-died-every-year-average-exposure-to-the-cold%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Meanwhil