%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine%20floats%20the%20theory%20it%20may%20have%20been%20tricked%20into%20shooting%20down%20the%20plane%20Russia%20says%20was%20full%20of%20Ukrainian%20POWs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20air%20crash%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b23e276c8f0a134f79eacf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESecurity%20measures%20are%20taken%20after%20an%20Il-76%20plane%20with%2065%20Ukrainian%20military%20prisoners%20on%20board%20crashed%20on%20January%2024%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Russian%20military%20transport%20plane%20crashed%20Wednesday%20in%20a%20border%20region%20near%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussia%20accused%20Ukraine%20of%20shooting%20it%20down%2C%20killing%2074%20people%20on%20board%2C%20including%20prisoners%20of%20war.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine%20said%20it%20was%20not%20told%20about%20%26quot%3Bthe%20need%20to%20ensure%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20airspace%20in%20the%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20suggested%20that%20it%20may%20have%20been%20tricked%20into%20shooting%20down%20a%20plane%20that%20Russia%20claims%20was%20carrying%2074%20people%2C%20including%2065%20Ukrainian%20prisoners%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20said%20there%20were%20no%20survivors%20after%20an%20Il-76%20plane%20crashed%20near%20Yablonovo%2C%2044%20miles%20southeast%20of%20the%20Belgorod%20border%20region%20of%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20Telegram%20Wednesday%2C%20Ukraine's%20military%20intelligence%20(GUR)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.me%2FDIUkraine%2F3356%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20that%20Russia%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehad%20not%20requested%20safe%20passage%20for%20the%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20landing%20of%20a%20transport%20plane%20in%20a%2030-kilometer%20zone%20of%20hostilities%20cannot%20be%20safe%20and%20in%20any%20case%20must%20be%20discussed%20by%20both%20sides%2C%20because%20otherwise%2C%20it%20endangers%20the%20entire%20exchange%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20GUR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBased%20on%20this%2C%20we%20may%20be%20talking%20about%20planned%20and%20deliberate%20actions%20by%20the%20Russian%20Federation%20to%20destabilize%20the%20situation%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20weaken%20the%20international%20support%20for%20our%20state.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20Air%20Force%20Commander%20Mykola%20Oleshchuk%20said%20that%20Russia%20was%20seeking%20to%20undermine%20Ukraine's%20international%20support%20by%20exploiting%20the%20plane%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20the%20Jan.%2024%2C%202024%2C%20massive%20Russian%20propaganda%20targets%20external%20audiences%20with%20a%20flow%20of%20fake%20news%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20discredit%20Ukraine%20in%20front%20of%20the%20international%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20Oleshchuk%20wrote%20on%20his%20Telegram%20channel%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkyivindependent.com%2Fair-force-on-il-76-crash%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20Ukrainian%20media.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20well%20as%20prisoners%20of%20war%2C%20Russia%20said%20the%20plane%20was%20carrying%20six%20Russian%20crew%20and%20three%20escorts.%20It%20said%20its%20radar%20registered%20the%20launch%20of%20two%20missiles%20from%20Ukraine's%20Kharkiv%20region%20that%20borders%20Belgorod.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20could%20not%20confirm%20what%20caused%20the%20crash%20or%20who%20was%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feng.mil.ru%2Fen%2Fnews_page%2Fcountry%2Fmore.htm%3Fid%3D12497468%40egNews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20accused%20Ukraine%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20committing%20a%20%26quot%3Bterrorist%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20the%20plane%20was%20downed%20by%20anti-aircraft%20missiles%20fired%20from%20the%20village%20of%20Lyptsi%20in%20the%20Kharkiv%20region%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20military%20intelligence%20initially%20said%20the%20plane%20had%20been%20carrying%20Russian%20S-300%20air%20defense%20missiles%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pravda.com.ua%2Feng%2Fnews%2F2024%2F01%2F24%2F7438684%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%20Ukrainska%20Pravda.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20later%20statement%20from%20the%20intelligence%20directorate%20has%20been%20seen%20as%20a%20tacit%20admission%20that%20prisoners%20were%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20has%20called%20for%20an%20international%20investigation%20into%20the%20incident%20and%20accused%20Russia%20of%20%26quot%3Bplaying%20with%20the%20lives%20of%20Ukrainian%20prisoners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKremlin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.com%2Fpolitics%2F1737119%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espokesman%20Dmitry%20Peskov%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20response%20said%20that%20if%20Zelenskyy%20had%20meant%20an%20investigation%20into%20%26quot%3Bthe%20criminal%20actions%20of%20the%20Kyiv%20regime%26quot%3B%20then%20it%20was%20definitely%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20unnamed%20US%20official%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Frussia-ukraine-crash-transport-plane-pows-0c878e65e1690c8857e314921a6b047a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20unclear%20whether%20there%20were%20Ukrainian%20POWs%20aboard.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20seen%20the%20reports%2C%20but%20we're%20not%20in%20any%20position%20to%20confirm%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20US%20National%20Security%20Council%20spokesman%20John%20Kirby%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-accuses-russia-tricking-it-into-shooting-down-pow-plane-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706188681000%2