s%20behaviour%20was%20particularly%20disparaging%20towards%20the%20elderly%20and%20those%20who%20could%20not%20speak%20English.%20He%20mentioned%20an%20incident%20wherein%20an%20elderly%20woman%2C%20who%20was%20not%20fluent%20in%20English%2C%20was%20pointing%20to%20the%20tea%20on%20the%20beverage%20cart%20and%20saying%20''Yes.''%20Instead%20of%20being%20understanding%20and%20handing%20her%20the%20beverage%2C%C2%A0a%20crew%20member%20almost%20yelled%20at%20her%C2%A0and%20asked%20her%20to%20%E2%80%9Copen%20your%20mouth%20and%20use%20your%20words.%E2%80%9D%20They%20also%20lectured%20customers%20about%20how%20they%20%26quot%3Bneed%20to%20wait%20their%20turn%26quot%3B%20when%20they%20asked%20for%20napkins.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20the%20full%20post%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-embed-height%3D%5C%22316%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Findia%2Fcomments%2F19efjkh%2Favoid_travelling_lufthansa%2F%5C%22%3EAvoid%20Travelling%20Lufthansa%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cnby%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fuser%2Fsazn2%2F%5C%22%3Eu%2Fsazn2%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Findia%2F%5C%22%3Eindia%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E''This%20same%20crew%20member%20went%20on%20a%20rant%20near%20me%2C%20talking%20to%20a%20customer%20about%20why%20they're%20ordering%20food%20if%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20eat%20it.%20This%20was%20comical%2C%20considering%20that%20Lufthansa%20had%20messed%20up%20the%20catering%20for%20the%20flights%2C%20and%20had%20made%20all%20the%20vegetarian%20dishes%20into%20vegan%20ones%2C%20which%20were%20almost%20inedible%20(I%20honestly%20do%20not%20know%20what%20happened%20or%20how.%20It%20was%20very%20confusing%2C''%20he%20further%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20mentioned%20another%20incident%20from%20the%20same%20flight%2C%20saying%20how%20a%20woman%20who%20ordered%20vegetarian%20food%20was%20served%20a%20chicken%20meal.%20''When%20she%20opened%20it%2C%20realized%20it%20was%20chicken%2C%20and%20asked%20a%20crew%20member%20to%20replace%20it%2C%20he%20said%20they%20couldn't%20replace%20it%20since%20she%20opened%20it%2C%20and%20went%20on%20to%20say%20%26quot%3Byou%20don't%20you%20to%20a%20restaurant%2C%20eat%20the%20food%20and%20ask%20for%20it%20to%20be%20taken%20back%2C''%20the%20post%20read.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBengaluru-based%20techie%20Shantanu%20Goel%20shared%20a%20screenshot%20of%20the%20Reddit%20post%20on%20X%2C%20where%20it%20has%20gone%20viral.%20''All%20this%20behavior%2C%20including%20downright%20rude%20and%20idiotic%20staff%20is%20unfortunately%20not%20an%20aberration%20but%20quite%20common%20on%20Lufthansa%2C%20which%20is%20why%20I%20never%20fly%20it%2C''%20Mr%20Goel%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20Indians%20shared%20similar%20experiences%20and%20raised%20allegations%20of%20racism%20against%20Lufthansa.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20the%20post%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EAll%20this%20behavior%2C%20including%20downright%20rude%20and%20idiotic%20staff%20is%20unfortunately%20not%20an%20aberration%20but%20quite%20common%20on%20Lufthansa%2C%20which%20is%20why%20I%20never%20fly%20it.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FbptvBxSEly%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FbptvBxSEly%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Shantanu%20Goel%20(%40shantanugoel)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fshantanugoel%2Fstatus%2F1750178745753948268%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2024%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20also%20caught%20the%20attention%20of%20Paytm%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Vijay%20Shekhar%20Sharma%20who%20quote-tweeted%20the%20post%20and%20wrote%2C%20'''Can't%20wait%20for%20Air%20India%20and%20Indigo%20to%20go%20places%20--%20many%20of%20us%20would%20rather%20not%20fly%20European%20airlines.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ECan't%20wait%20Air%20India%20and%20Indigo%20to%20go%20places%20--%20many%20of%20us%20would%20rather%20not%20fly%20Europian%20airlines.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FmVZxO1Qu6Z%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FmVZxO1Qu6Z%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Vijay%20Shekhar%20Sharma%20(%40vijayshekhar)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fvijayshekhar%2Fstatus%2F1750369094002442255%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2025%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EReacting%20to%20the%20post%2C%20one%20user%20wrote%2C%20''I%20had%20almost%20the%20same%20experience%20when%20I%20flew%20Luftansa%20once!%20Never%20touched%20them%20again.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20commented%2C%20''Time%20to%20do%20a%20%E2%80%98Maldives'%20on%20Lufthansa.''%20A%20third%20said%2C%20''Lufthansa%20and%20Air%20France%20are%20notorious%20for%20how%20they%20treat%20Indian%20patrons.%20Emirates%2C%20Air%20India%2C%20Etihad%2C%20and%20Singapore%20airlines%20are%20much%20better%20for%20Seniors%20in%20particular.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20third%20said%2C%20''The%20Lufthansa%20team%20attitude%20is%20extremely%20poor..it's%20just%20not%20a%20good%20airline%20to%20fly%20with.''%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706171940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-11%2Ftbnkpuo8_lufthansa-airlinesgeneric_625x300_06_November_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Favoid-travelling-redditor-accuses-lufthansa-staff-of-insulting-indians-paytm-ceo-reacts-4929200%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Reddit%20user%20mentioned%20several%20instances%20of%20the%20Lufthansa%20staff%20members%20discriminating%20against%20Indians%20and%20insulting%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Favoid-travelling-redditor-accuses-lufthansa-staff-of-insulting-indians-paytm-ceo-reacts-4929200%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Favoid-travelling-redditor-accuses-lufthansa-staff-of-insulting-indians-paytm-ceo-reacts-4929200%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Favoid-travelling-redditor-accuses-lufthansa-staff-of-insulting-indians-paytm-ceo-reacts-4929200%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Pakistan's%20Forthcoming%20Elections%20Will%20Mean%20for%20Political%20Instability%20and%20Military%20Control%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25140239%2FPakistan-elections.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Pakistan%20prepares%20to%20go%20ahead%20with%20its%2014th%20general%20election%20on%20February%208%2C%202024%2C%20the%20denial%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98bat%E2%80%99%20symbol%20to%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20Pakistan%20Tehrik%20e%20Insaf%20(PTI)%20party%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(SC)%20on%20January%2013%20has%20cast%20fresh%20doubts%20about%20its%20credibility%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20level%20playing%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20held%20in%20July%202018%2C%20the%20elections%20have%20been%20delayed%2C%20not%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20After%20Zia%20ul%20Haq%E2%80%99s%20martial%20law%20in%201977%2C%20despite%20assuring%20%E2%80%98elections%20after%2090%20days%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20deadline%20kept%20getting%20extended.%20Neither%20have%20they%20been%20completely%20%E2%80%98free%20and%20fair%E2%80%99%2C%20with%20allegations%20surfacing%20every%20time%20about%20irregularities%20at%20the%20polling%20and%20counting%20stages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20clear%20constitutional%20violation%20this%20time%20too.%20Article%2051%20of%20the%201973%20Constitution%20stipulates%20these%20should%20be%20held%20within%2060%20days%20of%20the%20last%20National%20Assembly%20(NA)%20dissolution%2C%20which%20happened%20in%20early%20August%202023.%20A%20pretext%20for%20delay%20was%20provided%20by%20the%20mandatory%20requirement%20for%20delimitation%20of%20constituencies.%20The%20election%20schedule%20was%20notified%20finally%20in%20December%202023%2C%20with%20the%20chief%20justice%20sternly%20ordering%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%2C%20Sikander%20Sultan%20Raja%2C%20to%20take%20%E2%80%98lame-duck%E2%80%99%20President%20Arif%20Alvi%E2%80%99s%20(his%20five-year%20term%20ended%20in%20August%202023)%20approval%20for%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20minor%20flutter%20was%20caused%20on%20January%205%2C%202024%2C%20when%20a%20Senate%20resolution%20was%20suddenly%20passed%20to%20postpone%20the%20elections%2C%20on%20grounds%20of%20difficult%20weather%20conditions%20and%20adverse%20law%20and%20order%20situations%20prevailing%20in%20parts%20of%20Khyber%20Pakhtunkhwa%20(KP)%20and%20Balochistan.%20Tabled%20in%20a%20thinly%20attended%20session%20by%20an%20Independent%20Senator%2C%20Dilawar%20Hussain%2C%20it%20was%20passed%20by%20only%2012%20votes%20versus%202.%20Its%20legal%20effect%20remained%20doubtful%20as%20the%20prescribed%20quorum%20of%20the%20Senate%2C%20one%20fourth%20of%20its%20total%20membership%20of%20104%20i.e.%2026%2C%20was%20absent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20electorate%20comprises%20128.5%20million%20registered%20voters%2C%20out%20of%20a%20total%20population%20of%20241.5%20mn.%20The%20strength%20of%20the%20NA%20is%20now%20336%2C%20comprising%20266%20general%20seats.%20Sixty%C2%A0seats%20are%20reserved%20for%20women%20and%2010%20for%20non-Muslims.%20These%20are%20allotted%20to%20political%20parties%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20proportional%20representation.%20The%20magic%20numbers%20for%20forming%20the%20government%20are%20134%20and%20169%2C%20after%20addition%20of%20reserved%20seats.%20Of%20the%20266%20general%20seats%20Punjab%20has%20141%2C%20Sindh%2061%2C%20Khyber%20Pakhtunkhwa%2045%2C%20Baluchistan%2016%20and%20the%20Federal%20Capital%20area%20of%20Islamabad%203%20seats.%20Punjab%20has%20more%20seats%20than%20the%20other%20three%20provinces%20combined.%20The%20party%20which%20controls%20Punjab%20controls%20Pakistan.%20This%20is%20a%20permanent%20feature%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20political%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20main%20political%20parties%20will%20be%20in%20the%20fray.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League%20(Nawaz)-PML(N)%20did%20well%20in%20the%20past%20in%20its%20main%20bastion%2C%20Punjab%2C%20where%20a%20supine%20bureaucracy%20and%20%3Cem%3Ebiradari%3C%2Fem%3E%20(sub-caste)%20affiliations%20helped%20it.%20While%20these%20still%20remain%20consequential%2C%20thrice%20Prime%20Minister%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20seemed%20rather%20listless%20since%20his%20return%20from%20almost%20four%20years%E2%80%99%20exile%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20obsessing%20mainly%20on%20past%20injustices%20against%20him%20by%20the%20courts%20and%20by%20insinuation%2C%20the%20military%20establishment.%20His%20dilemma%20has%20been%20to%20search%20for%20a%20counter%20narrative%20to%20offset%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20persisting%20popularity.%20Nawaz%20has%20also%20to%20decide%20who%20should%20inherit%20his%20mantle%2C%20charismatic%20daughter%20Maryam%20or%20docile%20brother%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%2C%20who%20remains%20more%20acceptable%20to%20the%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20of%20Pakistan%20(PPP)%20retains%20its%20main%20political%20base%20in%20Sindh%2C%20where%20it%20depends%20on%20support%20from%20rural%20landlords.%20It%20has%20lesser%20control%20in%20urban%20areas%20of%20Karachi%20and%20Hyderabad.%20After%20performing%20creditably%20as%20foreign%20minister%20in%20the%20last%20coalition%2C%20Bilawal%20Bhutto%20Zardari%20has%20been%20trying%20hard%20to%20enhance%20his%20acceptability%20to%20the%20Army%20as%20a%20young%2C%20articulate%2C%20balanced%20leader.%20Choosing%20to%20contest%20from%20Lahore%2C%20he%20has%20also%20tried%20to%20wrest%20back%20an%20erstwhile%20vote%20bank%20in%20Punjab.%20His%20father%2C%20Asif%20Zardari%2C%20is%20a%20more%20experienced%20and%20wily%20political%20leader.%20These%20two%20have%20been%20playing%20good%20cop%20and%20bad%20cop%2C%20occasionally%20criticising%20past%20allies.%20The%20latter%20has%20tried%20hard%20to%20stitch%20support%20from%20motley%20feudals%20in%20Balochistan%20and%20South%20Punjab%2C%20with%20possible%20stakes%20to%20become%20president%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistan%20Tehrik%20e%20Insaf%20(PTI)%20has%20its%20main%20stronghold%20in%20Khyber%20Pakhtunkhwa%20(KP)%2C%20holding%20government%20reins%20there%20since%202013.%20It%20made%20sizeable%20inroads%20in%20Punjab%20after%20Imran%20was%20thrown%20out%20of%20power%20by%20a%20vote%20of%20no%20confidence%20in%20the%20NA%20in%20April%202022%20by%20launching%20a%20narrative%20of%20%E2%80%98foreign%20conspiracy%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98unfair%20martyrdom%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98desertion%20by%20the%20military%20establishment%E2%80%99%20as%20reasons%20for%20his%20ouster.%20After%20the%20Punjab%20by-elections%20in%202022%2C%20he%20seemed%20electorally%20invincible.%20In%20a%20series%20of%20public%20meetings%2C%20senior%20military%20officers%20were%20disparaged%20by%20name.%20Though%20later%20exposed%20as%20false%2C%20this%20narrative%20has%20been%20fanned%20by%20an%20army%20of%20besotted%2C%20young%20social%20media%20trollers%2C%20who%20have%20now%20become%20a%20headache%20for%20Army%20censors!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20several%20derogatory%20audio%20and%20video%20disclosures%2C%20Imran%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20has%20not%20been%20affected%20by%20attempts%20to%20besmirch%20his%20character.%20Some%20Pakistani%20analysts%20try%20to%20explain%20this%20phenomenon%20as%20a%20political%20idea%2C%20facing%20unemployed%20youth%20in%20urban%20areas%20especially%2C%20that%20real%20power%20in%20Pakistan%20continues%20to%20lie%20with%20the%20GHQ%2C%20not%20with%20elected%20politicians%20or%20the%20Parliament.%20In%20Imran%E2%80%99s%20resurgence%2C%20they%20see%20their%20only%20redemption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20smaller%20parties%20like%20the%20Jamiat%20UIema%20e%20Islam%20(JuI-F)%20of%20Maulana%20Fazlur%20Rehman%20and%20the%20Balochistan%20Awami%20Party%20(BAP)%20have%20pockets%20of%20strength%20in%20southern%20KP%20%26amp%3B%20northern%20Balochistan.%20The%20Ishteqam%20e%20Pakistan%20Party%20(IPP)%2C%20a%20faction%20of%20the%20old%20PTI%20with%20sugar%20baron%20Jehangir%20Tareen%20as%20its%20leader%2C%20could%20win%20a%20few%20seats%20in%20Punjab%2C%20as%20may%20Pervez%20Khattak%E2%80%99s%20PTI%20(Parliamentarians)%20in%20KP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20the%20Karachi%20factor.%20This%20time%2C%20of%20Karachi%E2%80%99s%2021%20seats%2C%20the%20Muhajir%20Quami%20Movement%20(MQM)%2C%20which%20had%20pockets%20of%20strength%20in%20Greater%20Karachi%20in%20the%20past%2C%20is%20aiming%20for%2014-15%20seats%20to%20offset%20the%20PTI.%20Factions%20led%20by%20Khalid%20Maqbool%20Siddiqui%2C%20Farooq%20Sattar%20and%20Mustafa%20Kamal%E2%80%99s%20Pakistan%20Sarzameen%20Party%20(PSP)%20were%20herded%20together%20under%20the%20Army%E2%80%99s%20none%20too%20gentle%20prodding.%20However%2C%20this%20%E2%80%98union%E2%80%99%20has%20yet%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98blessed%E2%80%99%20from%20London%20by%20exiled%20MQM%20%E2%80%98imam%E2%80%99%2C%20Altaf%20Hussain.%20The%20Jamaat%20e%20Islami%20(JeI)%20could%20also%20try%20to%20build%20on%20its%20strong%20showing%20in%20the%20local%20body%20elections%20to%20win%20back%20a%20few%20of%20its%20traditionally%20held%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectable%20feudals%20from%20southern%20Punjab%20usually%20%E2%80%98go%20with%20the%20wind%E2%80%99.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20perception%20in%20Pakistani%20political%20circles%20initially%20suggested%20that%20the%20PML(N)%20was%20being%20favoured%20by%20the%20Army.%20However%2C%20with%20many%20Independents%20now%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20bets%20may%20be%20hedged%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98hung%E2%80%99%20parliament%20or%20a%20weak%20PML(N)-led%20option%20emerges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArmy%E2%80%99s%20compulsions%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArmy%20Chief%20General%20Asim%20Munir%20will%20seek%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20PTI%20does%20not%20win%20a%20majority.%20In%20June%202019%2C%20he%20was%20removed%20as%20Director%20General%2C%20Inter%20Services%20Intelligence%20(ISI)%20after%20a%20mere%20eight%20months%20on%20the%20job%2C%20when%20he%20complained%20to%20PM%20Imran%20about%20corruption%20by%20his%20wife%E2%80%99s%20relatives%20and%20friends.%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20entire%20strategy%20in%20the%20build%20up%20to%20the%20Army%20chief%E2%80%99s%20succession%20in%20November%2022%20focused%20on%20making%20it%20controversial%2C%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20getting%20his%20favourite%2C%20Lt%20Gen%20Faiz%20Hameed%2C%20Munir%E2%80%99s%20successor%20as%20DG%20(ISI)%2C%20to%20become%20the%20new%20chief.%20It%20was%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20who%20insisted%20that%20Munir%20should%20succeed%20General%20Bajwa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Chief%20of%20Army%20Staff%20(COAS)%2C%20Munir%20inherited%20a%20divided%20senior%20Army%20leadership.%20His%20retirement%20date%20as%20Lieutenant%20General%20had%20to%20be%20extended%20by%20two%20days%20to%20keep%20him%20senior%20most%20among%20contenders.%20Two%20of%20his%20peers%2C%20Lt%20Generals%20Azhar%20Abbas%20and%20Faiz%20Hameed%2C%20took%20premature%20retirement.%20Bajwa%20promoted%20and%20posted%2012%20new%20Lieutenant%20Generals%20just%20before%20he%20retired.%20Over%20the%20next%2012%20months%2C%20Munir%20has%20had%20to%20bide%20his%20time%2C%20to%20slowly%20get%20his%20own%20officers%20into%20plum%20positions.%20This%20included%20giving%20an%20extension%20to%20the%20current%20DG%20(ISI)%2C%20Lt%20Gen%20Nadeen%20Anjum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Imran%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20from%20a%20court%20in%20the%20Toshakhana%20(Treasury%20of%20State%20gifts%20chest)%20case%20on%20May%209%2C%202023%2C%20PTI%20supporters%20went%20on%20a%20rampage%2C%20attacking%20army%20installations%2C%20ISI%20offices%2C%20smaller%20air%20bases%20and%20monuments%20of%20martyrs%20country-wide.%20The%20chasm%20between%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20die-hard%20supporters%20and%20those%20who%20have%20traditionally%20venerated%20the%20Army%20as%20an%20institution%20widened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImran%20has%20been%20in%20prison%20since%20then%2C%20charged%20in%20a%20number%20of%20cases.%20The%20three%20main%20cases%20relate%20to%20the%20sale%20of%20costly%20watches%2C%20obtained%20from%20the%20Toshakhana%20for%20disproportionate%20personal%20benefit%2C%20cipher%20document%20misuse%2C%20land%20gift%20and%20a%20spurious%20trust%20formation%20from%20irregularly%20transferred%20funds%2C%20seized%20in%20the%20UK%20from%20Malik%20Riaz%2C%20a%20housing%20estate%20builder%20cum%20wheeler%20dealer.%20Imran%E2%80%99s%20nomination%20papers%20for%20the%20February%2024%20election%20have%20been%20finally%20rejected.%20He%20has%20also%20been%20arrested%20in%20the%20May%209%20violence%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDepriving%20PTI%20candidates%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98bat%E2%80%99%20symbol%20will%20be%20a%20big%20setback%20for%20them.%20They%20will%20now%20have%20to%20run%20as%20Independents.%20This%20may%20create%20confusion%20on%20polling%20day.%20Additionally%2C%20PTI%20will%20be%20ineligible%20to%20claim%20its%20proportion%20of%20reserved%20seats%20for%20women%20and%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPTI%20leaders%20may%20have%20tried%20a%20deliberate%20ploy%20to%20bring%20about%20an%20army-judiciary%20confrontation%2C%20two%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20institutions%20which%20have%20usually%20worked%20in%20consort%2C%20but%20it%20has%20not%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20sympathy%20of%20judges%20belonging%20to%20the%20Lahore%2C%20KP%20and%20Islamabad%20high%20courts%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20under%20previous%20CJ%2C%20Umar%20Ata%20Bandial%2C%20has%20been%20pronouncedly%20pro-Imran.%20The%20new%20CJ%2C%20Qazi%20Faiz%20Isa%2C%20enjoyed%20an%20upright%20reputation.%20The%20tenor%20of%20several%20of%20his%20past%20judgments%20has%20been%20against%20undue%20interference%20by%20the%20military%20establishment%20in%20civilian%20governance.%20Possibly%20for%20this%20very%20reason%2C%20he%20had%20to%20face%20a%20reference%20filed%20by%20the%20Imran%20Khan%20regime%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Judicial%20Council%20in%20May%2C%202019%2C%20under%20tacit%20military%20instigation.%20Isa%20may%20have%20an%20almost%20equal%20dislike%20for%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20return%20to%20power%20as%20the%20Army%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20his%20main%20focus%20has%20been%20to%20heal%20rifts%20within%20a%20hopelessly%20divided%20higher%20judiciary%2C%20an%20unpalatable%20bequest%20left%20for%20him%20by%20Bandial.%20Succour%20on%20this%20front%20has%20come%20recently%20with%20the%20resignations%20of%20Justices%20Mazhar%20Ali%20Naqvi%20and%20Izaz%20ul%20Ahsan%2C%20who%20was%20tipped%20to%20succeed%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20bat%20symbol%20judgment%20may%20have%20adversely%20affected%20his%20impartial%20image.%20Controversy%20abounds%20among%20legal%20eagles%20in%20Pakistan%20about%20its%20long-term%20implications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20intensifying%20trolling%20against%20CJ%20Isa%20and%20seeking%20a%20larger%20bench%20review%2C%20PTI%E2%80%99s%20plan%20will%20be%20to%20fall%20back%20on%20its%20social%20media%20organisers%20to%20correctly%20advertise%20the%20symbols%20allotted%20to%20its%20candidates%20left%20in%20the%20fray.%20Its%20supporters%20may%20still%20hope%20for%20a%20landslide%20turnout%20in%20PTI%E2%80%99s%20favour%20on%20election%20day%2C%20channelising%20widespread%20angst%20against%20the%20military%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98political%20engineering%E2%80%99.%20The%20possibility%20of%20PTI%20cadres%20indulging%20in%20sporadic%20violence%20on%20February%208%20also%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20scene%20remains%20gloomy%3Cstrong%3E.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Pakistani%20elite%2C%20comprising%20the%20civil-military%20gentry%20%E2%80%93%20landlords%2C%20big%20businessmen%2C%20generals%2C%20judges%20and%20civil%20servants%20%E2%80%93%20have%2C%20over%20decades%2C%20brought%20the%20country%20to%20this%20pass%2C%20living%20off%20international%20handouts%20to%20establish%20a%20rent-extraction%20economy.%20Pakistan%20witnessed%20low%20savings%20and%20investment%2C%20low%20import%20substitution%20and%20subsistence%20on%20low%20tax%20revenues.%20Perennial%20fiscal%20deficits%20and%20high%2C%20unproductive%20defence%20expenditures%20perpetuated%20what%20has%20been%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CPerfect%20Doom%20loop%E2%80%9D%20by%20Professor%20Atif%20Mian%2C%20well%20known%20Pakistani-origin%20economist%20at%20Princeton%20University%2C%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20financial%20risks%20involved%20in%20bailing%20out%20Pakistan%2C%20the%20IMF%20has%20released%20a%20second%20tranche%20of%20its%20next%20loan%20(%24700%20mn%20out%20of%20%243%20bn).%20Arduous%20loan%20repayments%20lie%20ahead.%20Food%20inflation%20persists%20at%20around%2028%25.%20General%20Asim%20Munir%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98zeal-%20driven%E2%80%99%20supervision%20of%20the%20Special%20Investment%20Council%2C%20set%20up%20to%20attract%20assistance%20from%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20old%20friends%20in%20the%20Islamic%20world%2C%20has%20not%20gathered%20much%20traction%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20backdrop%2C%20the%20February%208%20elections%20are%20unlikely%20to%20bring%20stability%20or%20reduce%20political%20confrontation%20in%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERana%20Banerji%20retired%20as%20Special%20Secretary%2C%20Cabinet%20Secretariat.%20This%20article%20is%20based%20on%20a%20talk%20at%20a%20Round%20Table%20at%20the%20National%20Security%20College%2C%20Australian%20National%20University%20(ANU)%2C%20Canberra%2C%20Australia%20on%20Jan%2024%2C%202024.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22publis