litics%2Fchart-ahead-of-indias-election-what-do-people-care-about%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Survey%20Finds%20False%20Information%20Risk%20Highest%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F06172515%2Ffakenews-fromfactcheckorg.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20unprecedented%20year%20for%20elections%2C%20false%20information%20is%20one%20of%20the%20major%20threats%20that%20people%20around%20the%20world%20will%20face%20according%20to%20experts%20surveyed%20for%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%E2%80%99s%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fpublications%2Fglobal-risks-report-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A02024%20Global%20Risk%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20following%20chart%20shows%20the%20varying%20degrees%20to%20which%20misinformation%20and%20disinformation%20are%20rated%20to%20be%20problems%20for%20a%20selection%20of%20analysed%20countries%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years%2C%20based%20on%20a%20ranking%20of%2034%20economic%2C%20environmental%2C%20geopolitical%2C%20societal%20and%20technological%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisinformation%20is%20defined%20as%20situations%20where%20the%20author%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apa.org%2Ftopics%2Fjournalism-facts%2Fmisinformation-disinformation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epurposefully%20sought%20to%20mislead%20their%20audience%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Misinformation%20describes%20information%20which%20is%20spread%20out%20of%20genuine%20belief%2C%20but%20can%20be%20just%20as%20harmful%20%E2%80%93%20like%20is%20sometimes%20the%20case%20with%20conspiracy%20theories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20the%20country%20where%20the%20risk%20of%20disinformation%20and%20misinformation%20was%20ranked%20highest.%20Out%20of%20all%20risks%2C%20misinformation%20and%20disinformation%20was%20most%20frequently%20selected%20as%20the%20number%20one%20risk%20for%20the%20country%20by%20the%20experts%2C%20coming%20before%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20illicit%20economic%20activity%2C%20inequality%20(wealth%2C%20income)%20and%20labour%20shortages.%20The%20South%20Asian%20nation%E2%80%99s%20next%20general%20election%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20held%20between%20April%20and%20May%202024%20in%20a%20country%20of%20some%201.4%20billion%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFake%20news%20had%20been%20rife%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%202019%20election%2C%20with%20%3Cem%3EVice%3C%2Fem%3E%20reporting%20how%20parties%20had%20%E2%80%9Cweaponised%20the%20platforms%20%5Bof%20Whatsapp%20and%20Facebook%5D%20to%20spread%20incendiary%20messages%20to%20supporters%2C%20heightening%20fears%20that%20online%20anger%20could%20spill%20over%20into%20real-world%20violence.%E2%80%9D%20More%20recently%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F25031%2Fcovid-19-misinformation-on-whatsapp-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emisinformation%20also%20became%20an%20issue%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20again%20via%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Ftopics%2F2018%2Fwhatsapp%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0WhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20following%20chart%20shows%2C%20other%20countries%20facing%20a%20high%20risk%20of%20the%20impacts%20of%20misinformation%20and%20disinformation%20are%20El%20Salvador%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Romania%2C%20Ireland%2C%20Czechia%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Sierra%20Leone%2C%20France%20and%20Finland%2C%20all%20with%20the%20threat%20considered%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%204th-6th%20most%20dangerous%20risks%20facing%20the%20country%20out%20of%2034%20in%20the%20coming%20two%20years.%20In%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20misinformation%2Fdisinformation%20is%20in%20rank%2011%20of%20the%20perceived%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWEF%20analysts%20conclude%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20presence%20of%20misinformation%20and%20disinformation%20in%20these%20electoral%20processes%20could%20seriously%20destabilize%20the%20real%20and%20perceived%20legitimacy%20of%20newly%20elected%20governments%2C%20risking%20political%20unrest%2C%20violence%20and%20terrorism%2C%20and%20a%20longer-term%20erosion%20of%20democratic%20processes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20data%20is%20based%20on%201%2C490%20expert%20opinions%20across%20academia%2C%20business%2C%20government%2C%20the%20international%20community%20and%20civil%20society%2C%20with%20a%20survey%20collected%20September%204%20to%20October%209%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20Statista.%20Find%20the%20chart%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F31605%2Frank-of-misinformation-disinformation-among-selected-countries%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706153086000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F06172515%2Ffakenews-fromfactcheckorg.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fsurvey-finds-false-information-risk-highest-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Out%20of%20all%20risks%2C%20misinformation%20and%20disinformation%20was%20most%20frequently%20selected%20as%20the%20number%20one%20risk%20for%20India%20by%20experts%2C%20coming%20before%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20illicit%20economic%20activity%2C%20inequality%20and%20labour%20shortages.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fsurvey-finds-false-information-risk-highest-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NATO's%20largest%20military%20exercise%20since%20Cold%20War%20kicks%20off%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706149822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22htt