s%20requested%20the%20Canadian%20government%20to%20provide%20information%20related%20to%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPursuant%20to%20its%20Terms%20of%20Reference%2C%20the%20Foreign%20Interference%20Commission%20has%20requested%20that%20the%20Government%20of%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20collection%20and%20production%20of%20document%20relating%20to%20paragraphs%20clause%20(a)(i)(A)%20and%20(a)(i)(B)%20of%20its%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.canada.ca%2Fen%2Fdemocratic-institutions%2Fgeneral%2Fterms-reference.html%5C%22%3ETerms%20of%20Reference%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%20information%20and%20documents%20relating%20to%20alleged%20interference%20by%20India%20related%20to%20the%202019%20and%202021%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20press%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Commission%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.canada.ca%2Fen%2Fdemocratic-institutions%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2Fgovernment-of-canada-launches-public-inquiry-into-foreign-interference.html%5C%22%3Elaunched%20in%20September%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20had%20explicitly%20mentioned%20that%20it%20would%20examine%20the%20interference%20by%20China%20and%20Russia%2C%20as%20well%20as%2C%20unnamed%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20actors%E2%80%9D%20may%20have%20engaged%20in%20the%20elections%20in%20the%20first%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20press%20release%20issued%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Commission%2C%20headed%20by%20a%20Judge%2C%20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20role%20of%20India%20is%20also%20part%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20September%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcanada-accuses-indian-government-of-assassinating-sikh-citizen-in-vancouver-expels-senior-diplomat%5C%22%3ECanadian%20prime%20minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20had%20publicly%20accused%3C%2Fa%3E%20India%20of%20being%20behind%20the%20shooting%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20Harpreet%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20who%20was%20proscribed%20as%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20by%20India